        },
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 2,
          "name": "LLP Agreement Change",
          "item": "https://www.patronaccounting.com/llp-agreement-change"
        },
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 3,
          "name": "LLP Agreement Change in Mumbai",
          "item": "https://www.patronaccounting.com/llp-agreement-change/mumbai"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Which ROC handles LLP agreement change in Mumbai?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "ROC Mumbai at Everest House, 100 Marine Lines processes Form 3, Form 4, Form 15, and Form 5 on MCA V3 portal. For business objects changes, ROC Mumbai reviews and approves. Patron's Marine Lines office adjacent to ROC for direct coordination."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is Form 3 and when must it be filed?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "MCA form for filing LLP Agreement and changes with ROC. Within 30 days of amendment. Late filing: Rs 100/day with no cap. For business objects change: approval-based (ROC reviews before approving). Other amendments: auto-approved. Patron files within 15 days."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do all partners need to agree?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Generally yes - all partners must consent unless existing agreement specifies different mechanism (e.g., majority for certain changes). Without specific provision, unanimous consent required under First Schedule. Patron reviews existing agreement's amendment provisions before initiating."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is a supplementary LLP agreement?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Legal document recording the amendment. Specifies: clauses changed, new terms replacing old, effective date, partner consent. Executed on Maharashtra non-judicial stamp paper (Rs 100-500 residual entry), signed by all partners, witnessed by 2 persons. Becomes part of original agreement."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is stamp duty required in Mumbai?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Supplementary deed on non-judicial stamp paper per Maharashtra Stamp Act. General amendments: Rs 100-500 (residual entry). Financial amendments (capital, significant monetary): may be higher based on value. Patron determines correct Maharashtra stamp duty for every amendment."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can business objects be changed?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Amend objects clause in supplementary deed, file Form 3. Important: Form 3 is approval-based for objects change. ROC reviews and may request additional documents. LLP cannot commence new activity until ROC approves. Processing: 10-30 days. Patron manages approval process."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the penalty for late Form 3?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Rs 100 per day with NO cap. Starts from 31st day after amendment. 6 months delay: Rs 18,000. 1 year: Rs 36,500. Non-filing also creates MCA compliance gap blocking other filings (Form 8, Form 11). Patron files within 15 days to prevent all penalties."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can multiple amendments be combined?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Multiple changes made simultaneously can be combined in single supplementary deed and single Form 3. If different effective dates needed: separate filings. Patron advises Mumbai LLPs on bundling vs separate filings for efficiency."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}</script>

