<!-- SECTION 4: WHO CAN FILE -->
<section class="content-section" id="who-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">When Mumbai LLPs Need Agreement Changes</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p><strong>Profit-sharing ratio revision</strong> &ndash; Most common for BKC professional LLPs. Partners' contributions change over time. Updated in supplementary deed + Form 3. Section 40(b) IT Act limits on deductible remuneration must be considered. Patron drafts with tax-efficient structuring.</p>
                <p><strong>Capital contribution increase</strong> &ndash; Growing LLPs need more working capital. Supplementary deed records new amounts, timeline, revised capital accounts. Common for Powai tech LLPs scaling. For foreign partners: <a href="/fdi-compliance">FEMA LLP-I</a> additionally required.</p>
                <p><strong>Business objects/activity addition</strong> &ndash; Adding new service line or business. Form 3 is approval-based &ndash; ROC must approve before LLP can commence. 10-30 days processing. Patron handles approval follow-up.</p>
                <p><strong>Partner admission or retirement</strong> &ndash; New partner joins or existing partner exits. Supplementary deed + Form 3 + Form 4 filed together. Settlement for retiring partner documented. Common at Fort family LLPs and BKC professional firms.</p>
                <p><strong>Governance restructuring</strong> &ndash; Voting thresholds, committees, designated partner powers, decision-making changes. As LLPs mature. Nariman Point investment advisory and BKC multi-partner firms frequently restructure.</p>
                <p><strong>Registered office or name change</strong> &ndash; Office relocation: Form 3 + Form 15. Name change: RUN-LLP + Form 5 + Form 3. Post-amendment: update PAN, GST, bank, all registrations. Patron coordinates the complete process.</p>

            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

