<!-- SECTION 8: DOCUMENTS REQUIRED -->
<section class="content-section" id="documents-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Documents Required for LLP Agreement Change in Mumbai</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Existing LLP Agreement:</strong> Original + all previous amendments for reference and clause numbering</li>
                    <li><strong>Supplementary LLP Agreement:</strong> On Maharashtra non-judicial stamp paper, signed by all partners, witnessed by 2</li>
                    <li><strong>Partner Resolution/Consent:</strong> Written consent of all partners approving the amendment</li>
                    <li><strong>DSC of Designated Partner:</strong> Valid Digital Signature for MCA filing</li>
                    <li><strong>LLPIN:</strong> LLP Identification Number for Form 3 filing</li>
                    <li><strong>Supporting Documents:</strong> Address proof (office change), new partner DPIN/PAN (admission), RUN-LLP approval (name change), new activity description (objects change)</li>
                    <li><strong>Maharashtra Stamp Paper:</strong> Non-judicial stamp paper of requisite value</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:16px;">
                    <p><strong>Mumbai-Specific Tip:</strong> Maharashtra stamp duty on LLP supplementary agreements falls under the residual entry (Rs 100-500). For amendments involving capital contribution changes or significant financial terms, higher duty may apply based on value. Patron determines the correct Maharashtra stamp duty for every amendment to prevent insufficiency issues.</p>
